11 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Water Resources
Board; making an appropriation; requiring that
12 portions of certain appropriated funds be used for
certain purposes; providing an effective date; and
13 declaring an emergency.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Water
18 Resources Board from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
19 General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the fiscal year
20 ending June 30, 2027, the sum of Nine Hundred Twenty-five Thousand
21 Dollars ($925,000.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary to
22 carry out the provisions of Enrolled Senate Bill No. 259 of the 2nd
23 Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature.
24
SB1175 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 SECTION 2. From the funds appropriated to the Oklahoma Water
2 Resources Board in Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session
3 of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the Board shall deposit the sum of
4 Ten Million Dollars ($10,000,000.00) to the Rural Economic Action
5 Plan Water Projects Fund (225), created pursuant to Section 2002.1
6 of Title 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes. The Board may enter into
7 contracts with financial institutions and execute such instruments
8 as may be necessary to hold and disseminate loan funds in accordance
9 with applicable regulations and Board policies.
10 SECTION 3. From the funds appropriated to the Oklahoma Water
11 Resources Board in Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session
12 of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the sum of Two Million Dollars
13 ($2,000,000.00) shall be used for a project to design a regional
14 water system in northeast Oklahoma.
15 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
16 SECTION 5. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
17 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
18 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
19 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
20
21 DIRECT TO CALENDAR.
